---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service — Timetz"
  description="Timetz terms of service. Free to use, no account required. Read the full terms before using the site."
>
  <header class="app-header">
    <div class="app-header-inner">
      <a href="/" class="app-logo-link">
        <img src="/favicon-96x96.png" alt="timetz logo" class="app-logo-img" />
        <span class="app-logo-text">timetz</span>
      </a>
      <button class="theme-toggle" id="theme-toggle" aria-label="Toggle theme" title="Toggle light/dark">
        <span class="theme-icon-dark">🌙</span>
        <span class="theme-icon-light">☀️</span>
      </button>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="legal-page">
    <div class="legal-inner">
      <nav class="legal-breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span>Terms of Service</span>
      </nav>

      <header class="legal-header">
        <p class="legal-eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="legal-title">Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="legal-meta">Effective date: 1 June 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Last updated: 23 June 2026</p>
        <p class="legal-summary">
          Short version: Timetz is a free tool — use it, don't abuse it, and don't hold us liable for clock-related disasters.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="legal-body">

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>1. Acceptance of terms</h2>
          <p>
            By accessing or using <strong>timetz.com</strong> ("the Service"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service
            ("Terms"). If you do not agree, please do not use the Service. These Terms apply to all visitors and users.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>2. Description of service</h2>
          <p>
            Timetz is a free, browser-based utility for converting times between timezones and cities worldwide.
            It uses publicly available IANA timezone data and does not require registration or payment.
            The Service is provided as-is for personal, commercial, and educational use.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>3. Permitted use</h2>
          <p>You may use Timetz to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Convert and compare times across any number of timezones.</li>
            <li>Plan meetings, calls, and events across geographies.</li>
            <li>Embed or link to timetz.com from other websites or apps.</li>
            <li>Access the Service via browser automation or scripting for personal or internal business use.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>4. Prohibited use</h2>
          <p>You may not:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Use automated tools to scrape, crawl, or bulk-download the Service in a way that degrades performance for other users.</li>
            <li>Attempt to gain unauthorised access to any system, server, or database associated with the Service.</li>
            <li>Reverse-engineer, decompile, or otherwise attempt to extract source code for commercial redistribution without permission.</li>
            <li>Use the Service for any purpose that violates applicable law or regulation.</li>
            <li>Impersonate Timetz or claim any official affiliation with the Service.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>5. Accuracy of information</h2>
          <p>
            Timetz relies on the IANA timezone database, which is widely regarded as the authoritative source
            for timezone and DST rules. However, governments can and do change timezone rules with little notice.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>The Service is provided for informational convenience only.</strong> Timetz makes no warranty
            that timezone data is current, accurate, or complete for any specific jurisdiction at any specific moment.
            Do not rely solely on Timetz for legally binding deadlines, flight schedules, medication timing, financial
            transactions, or any situation where an error could cause harm.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>6. Intellectual property</h2>
          <p>
            The Timetz name, logo, and original source code are owned by the operator and may not be reproduced
            or redistributed without written permission. IANA timezone data is in the public domain.
            Typefaces used (Geist) are licensed under the SIL Open Font License.
          </p>
          <p>
            Nothing in these Terms restricts your right to use the <em>output</em> of the Service (i.e. the
            converted times you read on screen) for any purpose.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>7. Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
          <p>
            THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND,
            EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY,
            FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT.
            WE DO NOT WARRANT THAT THE SERVICE WILL BE UNINTERRUPTED, ERROR-FREE, OR FREE OF VIRUSES
            OR OTHER HARMFUL COMPONENTS.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>8. Limitation of liability</h2>
          <p>
            TO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, TIMETZ AND ITS OPERATOR SHALL NOT BE
            LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES ARISING
            FROM YOUR USE OF OR INABILITY TO USE THE SERVICE, EVEN IF ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY
            OF SUCH DAMAGES.
          </p>
          <p>
            IN ALL CASES, OUR TOTAL LIABILITY TO YOU FOR ANY CLAIM ARISING FROM THESE TERMS OR THE
            SERVICE SHALL NOT EXCEED USD $10 (TEN US DOLLARS).
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>9. Third-party links</h2>
          <p>
            The Service may contain links to external websites. These links are provided for convenience only.
            Timetz has no control over and accepts no responsibility for the content or privacy practices
            of any third-party site.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>10. Availability and modifications</h2>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to modify, suspend, or discontinue the Service (or any feature of it)
            at any time without notice. We are not liable to you or any third party for any such action.
            We also reserve the right to update these Terms at any time. The "Last updated" date at the
            top of this page will reflect any changes. Continued use of the Service constitutes acceptance
            of the revised Terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>11. Governing law</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms are governed by the laws of India, without regard to its conflict-of-law provisions.
            Any disputes arising from these Terms or your use of the Service shall be subject to the
            exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of India.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>12. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions about these Terms? Email <a href="mailto:hello@timetz.com">hello@timetz.com</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<script is:inline>
  (function () {
    const saved = localStorage.getItem('theme');
    const prefersDark = window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches;
    document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', saved || (prefersDark ? 'dark' : 'light'));
    const btn = document.getElementById('theme-toggle');
    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
      const next = document.documentElement.getAttribute('data-theme') === 'dark' ? 'light' : 'dark';
      document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', next);
      localStorage.setItem('theme', next);
    });
  })();
</script>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    min-height: 70vh;
    background: var(--bg);
    padding: 48px 24px 80px;
  }

  .legal-inner {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-breadcrumb {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-family: 'Geist Mono Variable', ui-monospace, monospace;
    color: var(--body);
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }

  .legal-breadcrumb a { color: var(--body); text-decoration: none; }
  .legal-breadcrumb a:hover { color: var(--cyan); }
  .legal-breadcrumb span:last-child { color: var(--ink); }

  .legal-header {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
    padding-bottom: 32px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .legal-eyebrow {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-family: 'Geist Mono Variable', ui-monospace, monospace;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--cyan);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin: 0 0 10px;
  }

  .legal-title {
    font-size: 36px;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -1px;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 10px;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .legal-meta {
    font-size: 13px;
    font-family: 'Geist Mono Variable', ui-monospace, monospace;
    color: var(--mute);
    margin: 0 0 18px;
  }

  .legal-summary {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--body);
    background: var(--cyan-dim);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--cyan);
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .legal-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 36px;
  }

  .legal-section h2 {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    letter-spacing: -0.2px;
  }

  .legal-section p,
  .legal-section li {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--body);
  }

  .legal-section p + p { margin-top: 12px; }

  .legal-section ul {
    padding-left: 20px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
    margin-top: 8px;
  }

  .legal-section a {
    color: var(--cyan);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .legal-section a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .legal-page { padding: 32px 16px 64px; }
    .legal-title { font-size: 26px; }
  }
</style>
